## 2. Core Concepts

| Concept | Description | Example |
|---------|-------------|---------|
| **Components** | Basic UI elements (buttons, labels, text fields, etc.). | `Button`, `Label`, `TextField` |
| **Containers** | Hold components and manage layout. | `Frame`, `Panel`, `Window` |
| **Layout Managers** | Control how components are arranged. | `BorderLayout`, `FlowLayout`, `GridLayout` |
| **Event Handling** | Respond to user actions (clicks, key presses). | `ActionListener`, `MouseListener` |
| **Graphics** | Drawing custom shapes or images. | `Graphics`, `Graphics2D` |

---

## 3. Building a Simple AWT Window

```java
import java.awt.*;
import java.awt.event.*;

public class SimpleAWTExample extends Frame implements ActionListener {
    Button btn;
    Label lbl;

    public SimpleAWTExample() {
        // Set up the frame
        setTitle("AWT Demo");
        setSize(300, 200);
        setLayout(new FlowLayout());

        // Create components
        lbl = new Label("Press the button");
        btn = new Button("Click Me");
        btn.addActionListener(this); // Register event handler

        // Add to frame
        add(lbl);
        add(btn);

        // Handle window close
        addWindowListener(new WindowAdapter() {
            public void windowClosing(WindowEvent e) {
                dispose(); // Close the window
            }
        });

        setVisible(true);
    }

    // ActionListener method
    public void actionPerformed(ActionEvent e) {
        lbl.setText("Button clicked!");
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        new SimpleAWTExample();
    }
}
```

**What this does:**

1. Creates a `Frame` (window).  
2. Adds a `Label` and a `Button`.  
3. Uses `FlowLayout` to arrange them.  
4. Handles button clicks via `ActionListener`.  
5. Closes the window cleanly with a `WindowListener`.

