## 8. Common Pitfalls & Fixes

| Issue | Fix |
|-------|-----|
| **Components not showing** | Ensure `setVisible(true)` is called after adding all components. |
| **Event not firing** | Verify listener is added to the correct component. |
| **Threadâ€‘safety** | GUI updates should happen on the Event Dispatch Thread (EDT). Use `EventQueue.invokeLater()`. |
| **Layout glitches** | Call `pack()` after adding components to let the layout manager size the frame automatically. |
| **Native lookâ€‘andâ€‘feel differences** | AWT uses OS widgets; if you need a consistent look, consider Swing or JavaFX. |

---

## 9. When to Use AWT vs. Swing vs. JavaFX

| Library | Strengths | When to Choose |
|---------|-----------|----------------|
| **AWT** | Lightweight, native widgets, minimal dependencies | Quick prototypes, legacy code, simple tools |
| **Swing** | Rich component set, customizable UI, no native widgets | Fullâ€‘featured desktop apps, crossâ€‘platform consistency |
| **JavaFX** | Modern UI, CSS styling, media support | Rich media apps, modern look, FXML for declarative UI |

